com.wizarpos.devices.contactlesscard
Interface ContactlessCardOperationResult

All Superinterfaces:
OperationResult
public interface ContactlessCardOperationResult
extends OperationResult

ContactlessCardOperationResults are generated by the ContactlessCard service implementation to notify the application of the completion of an operation.

The getStatus() method inherited from OperationResult is used to retrieve the success of the operation. Constants are defined in OperationResult for that purpose.

A second set of constants is defined starting in OperationResult and continued in this interface. These constants begin with "ERR_" and supply supplemental information via getInfo() when a status of EVT_ERROR is returned by getStatus().

static final int ERR_UNSUPPORTED_PARAM
Specified parameter is unsupported. Supplemental information constant for use with EVT_ERROR event status.

Used on completion of an open operation if the requested mode is unsupported for the requested logicalID, and also on completion of a scanTargets operation if unsupported parameters have previously been specified using addScanParam().
